President Obama issued a statement to thank Senator Herb Kohl for his 23 years of service in the United States Senate. He commended Kohl for his advocacy on behalf of working families, small business owners, and seniors. The President highlighted Kohl's efforts in areas such as childhood nutrition programs, food safety, affordable healthcare and childcare, and juvenile crime prevention. He also acknowledged Kohl's dedication to fostering the farming and manufacturing sector in Wisconsin and ensuring access to affordable prescription drugs for seniors. President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama expressed their gratitude to Senator Kohl and wished him and his family well in the future.